{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-prompt-rule-memo-task1-review.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Prompt Rule Memo Task 1 Review\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer (complete)`\n- bounded target: review whether the Prompt / Rule / Memo shell is distinct enough from agent cards\n\n## Completed\n\n- Reviewed the current Prompt / Rule / Memo shell against `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md` Task 1\n- Confirmed the three memory card types now exist as first-class cards rather than implicit agent metadata\n- Confirmed they are visually distinct from agent cards through dedicated panel placement, type-specific styling, and explicit placeholder state\n- Closed Task 1 and moved the track to a Task 2 source-integration audit\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- No code changes were made in this review slice\n- No packaging run was needed because extension behavior did not change\n- Deferred source integration, editing, and workflow linkage to later slices\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat Task 1 as complete once Prompt / Rule / Memo cards visibly exist and are distinguishable from agent cards\n- Move next to Task 2 instead of continuing to polish shell styling\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`. Stay on `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md` and do one Task 2 audit focused on the first smallest source-integration gap for Prompt / Rule / Memo cards.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
